#Text=The Minnesota Timberwolves ( 12 - 20 ) defeated the Utah Jazz ( 13 - 17 ) 94 - 80 on Wednesday in an offensive struggle .
#Text=This is certainly not the type of game that will make any highlight reel anytime soon .
#Text=Both teams played some horrendous offense and they may have set basketball back a few years .
#Text=Both of these teams have been struggling mightily coming into this game and it made this game hard to watch at times .
#Text=Utah was especially bad , as they shot 35 percent from the field and committed 19 turnovers in the loss .
#Text=The turnover differential was the key , as the Timberwolves commuted just 10 , which is almost half as many as the Jazz .
#Text=The Jazz had one of their worst offensive performances in franchise history and it 's clear the injuries are really starting to hurt this team .
#Text=It 's one thing to play without Rudy Gobert , but this offense has no punch without Derrick Favors and Alec Burks .
#Text=That can be exemplified by the fact that they started this game just 5 - for - 30 from the field and scored just 13 points in the first 14 minutes .
#Text=It 's not like it got much better after that though , as they failed to crack 21 points outside of the fourth quarter .
#Text=The lone bright spots were Trey Burke and Jeff Withey .
#Text=Withey tallied 13 points and nine rebounds filling in for Favors and Burke scored 23 points off the bench .
#Text=Utah will look to find some offense in their next game on Thursday against the Portland Trail Blazers .
#Text=While the Jazz offense was a nightmare , the Timberwolves played some of their best defense of the season here .
#Text=This marked the lowest point total the Wolves have allowed this season and it 's a good sign to see them play like this with their struggles at home all year .
#Text=Ricky Rubio did a great job of setting up the offense , as he dished out 17 assists to go along with 10 points in the win .
#Text=Rookie Karl Anthony-Towns recorded a double - double as well , tallying 25 points and 10 rebounds in the victory .
#Text=This wasn’t a pretty game by any means , but a win is a win .
#Text=Minnesota will look to keep up this defensive momentum on Thursday against the Detroit Pistons .
